# Connect the React app to the Node + MongoDB backend (see ../web technolagy/ from this folder) — required for real student ↔ host chat.
#
# Local: this repo includes .env.development so `npm run dev` already sets VITE_USE_API=true. Start the API in ../web technolagy (npm start, port 3000).
# Vite proxies /api → localhost:3000; leave VITE_API_BASE_URL unset locally unless you point at a remote API.
# To override locally only, copy lines into .env.development.local (gitignored).
#   VITE_USE_API=true
#
# Render STATIC SITE (build-time — set in Environment, then redeploy — values are baked into the JS bundle):
#   VITE_USE_API=true
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://YOUR-BACKEND-SERVICE.onrender.com
# No trailing slash on the URL. On the API Web Service set CLIENT_ORIGIN to your static site origin for CORS + cookies.
